  overviewText="Today's dentures are dramatically better than the appliances of a generation ago. Using advanced acrylic resins, digital measurements, and careful bite analysis, we create dentures that fit snugly, resist movement during eating and speaking, and look like a natural set of teeth. Full dentures replace an entire arch; partial dentures fill gaps when healthy teeth remain. For patients who want the stability of fixed teeth without individual implants, implant-supported dentures snap onto two to four implant posts — eliminating movement and dramatically improving chewing force."
  overviewExtra="Patients from Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck who need dentures often come to us after experiences with poorly fitting appliances elsewhere. At Thrive Dental, we take the time to get the fit right — which means multiple try-in appointments before the final denture is delivered, thorough bite adjustment at delivery, and follow-up visits to refine fit as your gum tissue adapts. If you've been told dentures are your only option but you'd prefer something more permanent, ask us about implant-supported dentures or individual implants — there are more options available than most patients realize, and we'll always give you the full picture before you decide."
